<h2>American Indian Parent Network</h2>

<p>Did you know that the dropout rate for American Indian  students is the highest in the state for any minority group? About 60 percent  of American Indian students drop out of school before reaching graduation. Both  federal and state laws mandate that American Indian children must receive  education that acknowledges their heritage and culture.
</p>
<p>Would you like information about education or mental health services? Do you need to know more about your child's special education program or Section 504 accommodations? Do you have questions about school discipline? Are you unsure of your rights? </p>
<p>
If so, the American Indian Parent Network can help! The American Indian Parent Network provides workshops and individual assistance to parents and professionals, including those from the Bureau of Indian Affairs and tribal and charter schools.
</p>

<h3 style="margin-bottom: 1em;">The American Indian Parent Network offers:</h3>

